gredients" content="1 tbsp oil">1 tbsp oil</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 onion, roughly chopped">1 <a href="/glossary/onion" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">onion</a>, roughly chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary"><article id="node-253826" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/onion"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/onionchop.jpg?itok=Z9o7wXeU" width="100" height="100" alt="Onion" title="Onions are endlessly versatile and an essential ingredient in countless recipes" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/onion">Onion</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">un-yun</span><p>Onions are endlessly versatile and an essential ingredient in countless recipes. Native to Asiaâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 large potato, chopped into small chunks">1 large <a href="/glossary/potato" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">potato</a>, chopped into small chunks<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-259416" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/potato"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/potatoes.jpg?itok=RkMk9Ubx" width="100" height="100" alt="Potato" title="The world&#039;s favourite root vegetable, the potato comes in innumerable varieties" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/potato">Potato</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">po-tate-oh</span><p>The world's favourite root vegetable, the potato comes in innumerable varieties. A member ofâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 aubergine, trimmed and chopped into chunks">1 <a href="/glossary/aubergine" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">aubergine</a>, trimmed and chopped into chunks<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-252041" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/aubergine"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/aubergine.jpg?itok=PXsgi_ZB" width="100" height="100" alt="Aubergine" title="Although it&#039;s technically a fruit (a berry, to be exact), the aubergine is used as a vegetable" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/aubergine">Aubergine</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">oh-ber-geen</span><p>Although it's technically a fruit (a berry, to be exact), the aubergine is used as aâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="250g button mushrooms">250g button <a href="/glossary/mushroom" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">mushrooms</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-260766" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/mushroom"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/mushroom-crop.jpg?itok=DHZa81Aq" width="100" height="100" alt="Mushroom" title="Mushroom" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/mushroom">Mushroom</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">mush-room</span><p>The mushroom is a fungus which comes in a wide range of varieties that belong to two distinctâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2-4 tbsp curry paste (depending on how hot you like it)">2-4 tbsp curry paste (depending on how hot you like it)</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="150ml vegetable stock">150ml vegetable stock</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="400ml can reduced-fat coconut milk">400ml can reduced-fat <a href="/glossary/coconut-milk" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">coconut milk</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-6703321" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/coconut-milk"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/08/coconut-milk-2.jpg?itok=HPq83s2g" width="100" height="100" alt="Coconut milk in a glass, with half a coconut " title="Coconut milk " /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/coconut-milk">Coconut milk</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ko-ko-nut mill-k</span><p>Coconut milk is not the slightly opaque liquid that flows from a freshly opened coconut â€“â€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="chopped coriander, to serve">chopped coriander, to serve</li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat the oil in a large saucepan, add the onion and potato. Cover, then cook over a low heat for 5 mins until the potatoes start to soften. Throw in the aubergine and mushrooms, then cook for a few more mins.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Stir in the curry paste, pour over the stock and coconut milk. Bring to the boil, then simmer for 10 mins or until the potato is tender. Stir through the coriander and serve with rice or naan bread.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1146438000" class="text-style-alt">May 2006</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div><div class="recipe__tips"><div class="field field-name-field-bbcgf-tips field-type-entityreference field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><div class="view view-recipe-views view-id-recipe_views view-display-id-tips view-dom-id-0fd848ea27f0ab9197f08a20c6febaa6"><div class="view-content"><div class="carousel-tips__wrapper carousel"><div class="flexslider carousel-tips__elements" data-type="carousel-tips"><ul class="slides carousel-tips__slides"><li class="carousel-tips__single-slide "><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-content"><h3>Recipe Tip</h3><h4><span class="field-content">Make it vegan</span></h4><div class="carousel-tips__single-slide-body show-more__content">Just substitute your favourite vegan brand of curry paste.</div></div></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-102509" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/recipe_images/recipe-image-legacy-id--513540_11.jpg?itok=gfd7PO6_" width="324" height="294" alt="Sweet potato, chickpea &amp; chorizo hash" title="Sweet potato, chickpea &amp; chorizo hash" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/725646/sweet-potato-chickpea-and-chorizo-hash"> Sweet potato, chickpea &amp; chorizo hash </a></h3><div class="push-item__ratings"><div class="clearfix fivestar-average-stars fivestar-average-text"><div class="fivestar-static-form-item"><div class="form-item form-type-item"><div class="field-main"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">4.160255</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></di