text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">was delicious. In future, I would double the mushrooms as it felt overloaded with potato and aubergine. Would also add a thickening agent to the sauce. Agree with others I doubled the time of simmering to make sure the potatoes were soft enough.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1039456"><a id="comment-1039456"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"><div class="user-picture"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/avatar/public/pictures/picture-6585506-1517332969.jpg?itok=1IQxvvH_" width="40" height="40" alt="Adrian Tupper&#039;s picture" title="Adrian Tupper&#039;s picture" /></div></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">Adrian Tupper</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 30th Jan, 2018</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">3.8</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Substituted courgette for aubergine. The sauce tasted fine, but very runny and pale rather than dark and thick as in the picture. And yes, either simmer for longer as I did or par-boil the potatoes.
Didn't want to add cornflour as others have suggested, as this makes a curry taste more like a Homepride cook-in sauce!!! Perhaps bash a few potatoes to thicken it.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1038311"><a id="comment-1038311"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">isawahatonce</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 24th Jan, 2018</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">3.8</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">very nice but needed alterations from the recipe - specifically par-boiling the potatoes for about 8 minutes and I just put a stock cube in rather than making stock so that it wouldn't be so watery</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1024396"><a id="comment-1024396"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">daviddyer</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 18th Nov, 2017</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">3.8</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Just made this very quick and very simply curry. Used small potatoes and par boiled them first, added some peas and kidney beans. I have enough left for tomorrow tea! I used Jalfrezi paste and it was fantastic with some brown rice.
