field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Lovely recipe for our Meat-Free Monday. After reading the comments I tweaked the recipe slightly - we used sweetcorn and green beans instead of aubergine, added a clove of garlic with the onions and potatoes, and stirred the balti curry paste with the stock and added a tablespoon of tomato puree before adding to the pan. We also cooked the curry for about 30 minutes and the potatoes were cooked but still held their shape.
Next time we may sautÃ©e the potatoes and have the curry poured over them, for a bit of texture.
All in all, a lovely simple recipe.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1001061"><a id="comment-1001061"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">rachelleason23</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 6th Jul, 2017</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">3.8</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="off"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Just made, was very very nice if a little watery but the rice soaked up most of the moisture.
