der, you&#39;ll need to experiment with quantities, starting perhaps with a couple of teaspoons. If you do use powder, cook it for 1 -2 mins to release the flavours. Let us know how you get on!</div></div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-698746"><a id="comment-698746"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">Phoenixphire</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 6th Oct, 2013</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Is there something I can use as a substitute for the coconut milk? Or maybe just leave it out? My husband is allergic to coconuts.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div></div></div></div><div id="fragment-tip" class="section-comments__single-tab-content"><div class="view view-comment-views-comment-ajax view-id-comment_views_comment_ajax view-display-id-tip_page view-dom-id-28d7b5e7c6ba81608351e47ef36d9473"><div class="view-content"><div><div id="comment-wrapper-971816"><a id="comment-971816"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"><div class="user-picture"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/avatar/public/pictures/picture-5235766-1502571268.jpg?itok=uPNpUE6a" width="40" height="40" alt="AbiLewis96&#039;s picture" title="AbiLewis96&#039;s picture" /></div></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">AbiLewis96</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 11th Jan, 2017</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static